Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.88,0:00:04.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.45,0:00:07.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I bring you marvelous illusions \Nthat will make the night sparkle!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.67,0:00:11.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight's performance features the secret \Nof the Phantom Lady, unknown even to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.53,0:00:18.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mom, gimme a break already!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.99,0:00:22.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How many hours have you been\N yammering away now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.20,0:00:26.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? I haven't even gotten through half \Nthe subjects I want to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.42,0:00:28.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.10,0:00:29.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Kaito...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.28,0:00:32.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:34.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.67,0:00:36.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.55,0:00:38.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's something that's very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.93,0:00:43.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The story of how your \Nfather and I fell in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.61,0:00:45.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a sappy story...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.56,0:00:47.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.52,0:00:49.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No, nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.20,0:00:51.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll take it from the top once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.90,0:00:54.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Once was enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.64,0:00:56.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It all started 18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.67,0:01:00.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A Saturday night when the \Nfull moon was bright...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.20,0:01:03.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never forget that kiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.25,0:01:05.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was so thrilling and romantic...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.87,0:01:07.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.37,0:01:08.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That time already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.96,0:01:11.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom, I gotta go!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.30,0:01:13.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.88,0:01:15.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.94,0:01:19.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is one of my \NKid the Phantom Thief nights!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.13,0:01:25.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Darling...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.39,0:01:26.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.95,0:03:11.96,Signs - Thief Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,0)}Enter: The Phantom Lady
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.43,0:03:13.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.55,0:03:16.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.45,0:03:20.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Nakamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.94,0:03:25.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief has stolen the \Njewel and escaped into the crowd!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.64,0:03:28.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Inspector, Kid is using a hang glider...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.41,0:03:30.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's his usual decoy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.58,0:03:33.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let anybody out of the museum \Nuntil they've had a full body check!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.57,0:03:36.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't I leave?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.94,0:03:39.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't hurry, Kid's gonna get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.69,0:03:42.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.81,0:03:45.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Nakamori Aoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.09,0:03:48.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just came to drop off my \Ndad's dinner! Can't I go home?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.36,0:03:51.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.36,0:03:53.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Inspector Nakamori's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.54,0:03:54.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.82,0:03:56.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,P-Pardon me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.84,0:03:59.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay. Keep up the good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.38,0:04:03.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.13,0:04:12.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Aoko! I borrowed your face again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.14,0:04:17.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, looks like it's not the \Njewel I'm {\i1}really{\i0} after...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:21.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll send this one back \Nto Inspector Nakamori, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.91,0:04:24.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, this is curious...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.11,0:04:28.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A sticker with a message was \Non the bottom of the jewel...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.44,0:04:34.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief, it's my turn next.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.62,0:04:37.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Saturday night, under the full moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.57,0:04:41.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall seize the jewel upon the \Nhead of the untarnished nail
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.41,0:04:44.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and thus repay the debt I owe you \Nfrom 18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.33,0:04:47.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.97,0:04:51.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"The head of the untarnished nail"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.12,0:04:54.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't even born 18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.31,0:04:58.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't know, but they \Nprobably have the wrong guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.72,0:05:03.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. This'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.72,0:05:03.57,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakamori Ginzo-dono\NMetro Police Dept., Second Investigation Division
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.18,0:05:17.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He makes his way through tight security \Nas if performing a magic trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.17,0:05:20.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Magician Under the Moonlight... \NKid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.16,0:05:22.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How does he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.24,0:05:29.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is a person who can walk right through \Nthat tight net without being checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.12,0:05:31.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.20,0:05:34.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Nakamori Aoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.91,0:05:41.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The world's greatest thief and this girl seem \Nto have a close relationship, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.52,0:05:43.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But, President Gouzu,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.72,0:05:48.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,she's the daughter of Inspector Nakamori \Nfrom the Second Investigation Division.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.68,0:05:52.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid probably just disguised himself \Nas her because it was convenient...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.25,0:05:54.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This would make the fifth such occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.75,0:05:59.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Then Kid and the daughter of the inspector \Nin charge of catching him are...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.52,0:06:00.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.78,0:06:03.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that {\i1}is{\i0} the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.58,0:06:10.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magicians use the psychology of disbelief \Nto pull pigeons out of impossible places,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:12.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,much to our bafflement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.64,0:06:15.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.97,0:06:22.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you suppose Kid returns most of the \Njewels he steals to Inspector Nakamori?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.15,0:06:27.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,True. He could just as well return them to \Nother detectives or who he stole them from.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.77,0:06:31.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But some of those people might not be honest \Nabout getting the jewels back from Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.74,0:06:36.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Kid trusts \NInspector Nakamori.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.08,0:06:37.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.28,0:06:44.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakamori Ginzo controls Kid the \NPhantom Thief from behind the scenes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.44,0:06:50.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He made his daughter inherit the role \Nof Kid, prepares her escape routes,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.55,0:06:54.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and has her return\N the stolen gems to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.06,0:06:58.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This also explains why he \Nfails to catch Kid every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.27,0:07:03.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that girl's been seen many times \Nwhile Kid's been pulling a robbery!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.50,0:07:05.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a stand-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.06,0:07:12.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Given her skills, it would be a simple feat \Nto employ another girl to dress up as her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.24,0:07:15.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But then what are they after?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.04,0:07:21.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All I know is that I've suffered \Nfor 18 long years thanks to Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.60,0:07:25.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.86,0:07:27.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The bait has been put out,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.80,0:07:32.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and soon I'll reveal that Kid is working \Nfor her father, Inspector Nakamori,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.43,0:07:36.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and that under that cape and tux is \Nan average high school student!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.80,0:07:40.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.88,0:07:43.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.00,0:07:44.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I think of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.66,0:07:46.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As always, your chest hasn't developed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.69,0:07:49.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The hairpin, you dope, the hairpin!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.40,0:07:50.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's cute, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.74,0:07:53.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure. Really cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.65,0:07:56.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make any unnecessary changes, dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.24,0:07:58.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're making it harder for me \Nto disguise myself as you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.92,0:08:03.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's hairpin's got an interesting shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.46,0:08:06.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's shaped like Toto Tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.59,0:08:08.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It came with the invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.59,0:08:09.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Invitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.98,0:08:17.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I won two tickets to a reserved dinner in \Nthe special observation platform of Toto Tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.70,0:08:21.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Special observation platform... \NIsn't that at the very top?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.62,0:08:27.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Having a delicious meal with a \Nbeautiful night view... I can't wait for Saturday!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.25,0:08:29.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But that special observation platform...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.85,0:08:34.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't they using it to exhibit some \Ndead rich guy's private collection?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.09,0:08:39.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw on the news that,\N just before he died,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.33,0:08:43.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,he bought a big-ass ruby that they're gonna \Nput on display from next week, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.54,0:08:45.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.04,0:08:50.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Kid is targeting that ruby, so \NI invited my dad so he can check it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.63,0:08:57.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but he said, "I'll be there on a stakeout \Nnext week anyway, so go with a friend!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.26,0:08:59.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Say no more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.04,0:09:01.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I can make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.21,0:09:02.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.62,0:09:04.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I beat you to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.71,0:09:06.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Akako?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.74,0:09:10.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That red tower was depressed after \NBell Tree Tower surpassed its height,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.81,0:09:16.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so given the "red" in my name, Akako, \NI'd feel bad if I didn't show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.00,0:09:20.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What, you wanted to go, Kaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.02,0:09:21.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Not especially!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.45,0:09:24.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad you don't get to case the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.00,0:09:28.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something fishy about the invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.93,0:09:32.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakamori-san said she doesn't \Nremember entering any contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.52,0:09:39.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe someone who knows about your other \Nidentity has set a trap, using her to lure you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.39,0:09:42.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, try not to stand out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.98,0:09:45.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like they say, the nail that \Nsticks out gets hammered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.64,0:09:47.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nail that sticks out...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.19,0:09:49.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.86,0:09:54.36,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue Parrot
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.46,0:09:54.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That does indeed sound suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.87,0:09:59.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Akako was right, that \Nsomebody's laying a trap for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.78,0:10:02.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Saturday night, under the full moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:07.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall seize the jewel upon \Nthe head of the untarnished nail,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.00,0:10:10.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and thus repay the debt I owe you \Nfrom 18 years ago."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.21,0:10:13.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.75,0:10:15.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Jii-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.96,0:10:20.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,18 years ago. That sticks in my mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.34,0:10:25.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it... \NWhere did I hear that recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.23,0:10:28.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That aside, did you get that \Nstuff together like I asked?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.73,0:10:30.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I prepared it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.52,0:10:32.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.44,0:10:36.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the outfit I need is all set!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.81,0:10:40.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. This time, the preparations were cheap.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.65,0:10:44.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that's his one good suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.65,0:10:46.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.20,0:10:49.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I never see him wear anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.58,0:10:53.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I was surprised!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.54,0:10:56.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When you suddenly said \Nyou could make it, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.83,0:11:01.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Given the occasion, Superintendent \NChaki insisted that I come.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.43,0:11:05.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Akako-kun. I'm sure you \Nwere looking forward to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.47,0:11:06.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.77,0:11:11.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I was looking out for you, jerk!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.36,0:11:13.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're killing my foot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:14.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Have fun,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.78,0:11:17.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,inspector with the crooked mustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.74,0:11:19.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mustache?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.05,0:11:21.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get pissed at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.94,0:11:28.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why, but the invitation \NAoko got may be a lure to get me here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.04,0:11:33.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.63,0:11:36.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So many things in the collection!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.16,0:11:38.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a museum in the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.40,0:11:45.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh, all of that fine art pales in \Ncomparison to this beautiful night view.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.73,0:11:50.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They say the owner of this \Ncollection loved Toto Tower
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.01,0:11:52.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and wanted to have an exhibition here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.12,0:11:55.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, nobody else is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.82,0:11:59.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we're having dinner here, you'd \Nthink there'd be a waitress at least...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.65,0:12:02.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like you can get in this car!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.64,0:12:07.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It says if you turn the key,\N the engine will roar!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.30,0:12:10.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,More like, the prerecorded \Nsound of an engine will play...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.74,0:12:14.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.59,0:12:16.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Exhaust is coming out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.17,0:12:18.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can this car move?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.24,0:12:22.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Aoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.72,0:12:27.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Handcuffs and knockout gas!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.84,0:12:29.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.48,0:12:31.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Long time no see,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.60,0:12:33.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.07,0:12:37.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,18 years, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.61,0:12:40.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.07,0:12:46.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Though you hung up your cape \Nand became a police inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.00,0:12:51.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, you had your snoozing daughter \Nover there inherit the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.79,0:12:53.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.79,0:12:56.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This guy's barking up the wrong tree!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.45,0:12:59.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But this situation feels familiar...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.40,0:13:00.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Deja vu?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.12,0:13:07.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this? Don't tell me you came here \Nnot realizing it was my trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.27,0:13:11.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The message on the jewel \Npointed to this place,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.89,0:13:15.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,while the invitation was an obvious trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.04,0:13:20.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all a contrivance so I could see what \Nyou would do before this, the final act.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.74,0:13:24.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it looks like I overestimated you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.65,0:13:29.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On a whim, I enclosed that hairpin \Nwith a bugging device inside of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.12,0:13:33.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but instead of destroying it, \Nyour daughter just put it in her hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.96,0:13:37.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it was a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.73,0:13:44.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The "head of the untarnished nail" refers to \Nthe head of a nail before a hammer hits it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.19,0:13:50.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the top of Toto Tower, \Nwhich escaped getting hammered
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.84,0:13:53.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,by the taller Bell Tree Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.89,0:13:58.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So you did catch the "nail that \Nsticks out gets hammered" reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.05,0:14:01.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But what are you going to do? The \Nsituation is just like in the old days,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.69,0:14:06.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but unlike then, your partner \Nhere isn't worth a damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.41,0:14:08.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.15,0:14:14.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Female with 20 Faces" who dropped \Nout of sight in Paris 18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.49,0:14:16.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The gentlewoman thief...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.88,0:14:20.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Phantom Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.50,0:14:23.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Phantom Lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.64,0:14:26.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! It's not deja vu!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.33,0:14:31.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the guy from 18 years ago... \NMom told me this story the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.99,0:14:37.56,Signs,,0000,0110,15,,{\a7}{\fad(500,0)}18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.02,0:14:43.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,15,,Hey! Hello? Hello? Hello?! What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.81,0:15:13.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.17,0:15:15.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Two...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.66,0:15:16.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.06,0:15:39.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As I figured...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.84,0:15:41.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.48,0:15:44.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bravo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.40,0:15:49.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a brilliant performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.62,0:15:56.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although using fake gore to scare a cop \Nto the point of fainting isn't my style.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.22,0:15:59.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would have gone with \Na more elegant method
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.46,0:16:02.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,to send them off to dreamland.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.81,0:16:04.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.09,0:16:07.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuroba Toichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.31,0:16:09.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a simple magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.90,0:16:16.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuroba Toichi. I know of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.29,0:16:21.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You traveled the world performing \Nmagic shows as a teenager,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.06,0:16:27.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and won first prize at the FISM tournament, \Nthe Magician Olympics, at the age of 20.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.34,0:16:29.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You were a prodigy when it came to magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.75,0:16:35.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But what's a celebrity like you \Ndoing in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.30,0:16:37.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And wearing such a flashy outfit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.47,0:16:42.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I had this suit custom-made for \Nmy magic show in Paris next month.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.37,0:16:48.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an homage to Arsene Lupin, \NFrance's great gentleman thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.36,0:16:53.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-He's casually walking over \Nwithout any night-vision goggles!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.76,0:16:57.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me he remembers the \Npositions of all the lasers?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.03,0:16:59.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're after...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.22,0:17:03.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...the motorcycle of the recently-departed \Nfamous French motorcycle racer,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.50,0:17:07.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,embedded with a diamond to \Ncommemorate his victories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.96,0:17:13.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The showpiece of the bike exhibition here\N on the top floor of {\i1}La Grande Dame de Fer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.98,0:17:17.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, that's a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.95,0:17:23.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Word gets out it's been stolen, and soon you \Ncan buy "the real one" on the black market.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.39,0:17:30.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Phantom Lady reappears after a two-year \Nabsence, but stealing this isn't worth your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.70,0:17:37.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What else can I do?! Somebody sent out a \Nnotice saying I was going to steal it tonight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.66,0:17:39.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can give me the details later.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.58,0:17:41.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me drop you off downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.28,0:17:45.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot. I'm riding this out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.04,0:17:48.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Replica or not, I'm delivering \Nit to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.96,0:17:50.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't do that if I were you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.12,0:17:54.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See? What'd I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.78,0:17:56.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's with the handcuffs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.78,0:18:00.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It means I have no more use for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.49,0:18:04.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You should've stayed home, \Ngloating over all the stolen jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.94,0:18:09.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But instead, you kept returning \Nthe loot to the police,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.78,0:18:15.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,putting a major dent in my business as I got \Nall these replicas in stock but no buyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.19,0:18:16.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:19.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know you worked with assistants.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.69,0:18:21.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's no assistant of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.28,0:18:26.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, if the Phantom Lady is \Ncaptured stealing the treasure,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.05,0:18:28.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,doesn't that put a crimp \Nin your plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.18,0:18:30.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No worries there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.72,0:18:36.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already got a trained Phantom Lady \Nimpersonator on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.29,0:18:39.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And no sense having two of you, \Nso you'll disappear for good...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.10,0:18:46.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.64,0:18:47.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.87,0:18:50.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the only exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.16,0:18:54.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we block the elevator, \Nthey've got no way out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.18,0:18:56.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.87,0:19:06.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.96,0:19:09.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.73,0:19:11.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.22,0:19:13.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm dropping you off at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.17,0:19:15.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dropping me off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.05,0:19:16.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're just falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.96,0:19:20.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,First, I'll silence that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.95,0:19:22.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...annoying sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.07,0:19:33.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As I suspected, there was a jewel...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.94,0:19:36.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...behind that mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.98,0:19:39.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you talking like an idiot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.53,0:19:42.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You, me, and the motorcycle \Nare going to hit the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.48,0:19:45.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.16,0:19:48.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.22,0:19:59.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Toichi-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.92,0:20:04.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As you requested, I staged an \Naccident to seal off the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.57,0:20:08.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But many bystanders have cameras,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.12,0:20:11.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so I don't think you can use \Nthat costume for the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.87,0:20:13.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.20,0:20:17.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use this costume \Nas a phantom thief instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.32,0:20:24.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A thief so great that the world will \Nforget all about the Phantom Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.31,0:20:29.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'd like you to retire \Nfrom being a phantom thief
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.15,0:20:33.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and stay nice and safe \Nin my jewelry box.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.63,0:20:39.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't sound bad, \Nbut that jewelry box...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.42,0:20:43.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't any other \Njewels in it, are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.80,0:20:45.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.30,0:20:49.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! This situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.52,0:20:55.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like what Mom was gushing \Nabout, how she and Dad first met!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.35,0:20:58.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then this old fart is the guy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.53,0:21:02.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,whose crooked business was ruined \Nby Mom and Dad 18 years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:05.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what are you going to do,\N Kid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.59,0:21:09.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can try to escape in \Nthat car like 18 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.76,0:21:11.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,except it was a\N slim motorcycle then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.26,0:21:18.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That car is compact, but not enough to fit \Nthrough the windows of this observation deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.64,0:21:23.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, being a replica, \Nyou can't drive it in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.85,0:21:29.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Then this entire \Nprized collection is a hoax.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.35,0:21:33.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And as for the big-ass ruby coming \Nin next week, it's actually a fake
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.86,0:21:38.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that you'll say was stolen by Kid, \Nand then sell replicas on the black market.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.10,0:21:42.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all been arranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.53,0:21:54.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, things look a little \Ndicey for me there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.83,0:21:58.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The illusion must go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.42,0:23:33.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when I recall Mom's nostalgic tale,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.08,0:23:34.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I find myself in a big pinch in the present!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.94,0:23:40.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, if I can't slip out of this one, \NI don't have the right to succeed Dad as Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.10,0:23:43.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've gotta clean up the mess from \NMom's reckless behavior, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.48,0:23:46.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-oh! {\i1}He{\i0} showed up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.11,0:23:48.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then things definitely \Nwon't go according to plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.48,0:23:53.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on {\i1}Magic Kaito 1412{\i0}:\N Phantom Lady and the Ryoma Treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.48,0:23:53.07,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Phantom Lady and the Ryoma Treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.07,0:23:56.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Step right this way! Watch carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.20,0:23:58.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the illusion!
